00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:08.980
We will start with the definition
of a computer network.

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:13.820
A computer network is a set of nodes
connected by communication links.

00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:17.220
I repeat -- A computer
network is a set of nodes

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:18.920
connected by
communication links.

00:03:19.620 --> 00:03:23.480
To understand this definition,
I shall highlight the important words.

00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:25.560
They are the keywords
of this definition.

00:03:25.560 --> 00:03:28.920
The keywords are - nodes
and communication links.

00:03:28.920 --> 00:03:31.060
Firstly, we will concentrate on nodes.

00:03:31.720 --> 00:03:36.240
A node can be a computer,
printer or any other device

00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:38.320
capable of sending or receiving data.

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:43.700
Say you have a device, if that device
can send data or receive data

00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:45.700
or both send and
receive data,

00:03:45.700 --> 00:03:48.220
then we can call that
device as a node.

00:03:48.220 --> 00:03:52.220
So a node can be a computer,
printer or any device

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:54.920
but the important point
to note here is that

00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:58.440
device should be capable enough
in sending or receiving the data.

00:03:59.240 --> 00:04:01.380
We shall see some
examples for nodes.

00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:04.080
Obviously, a computer
is a node because

00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:07.000
a computer can send data
as well as receive data.

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:10.920
A server, printer,
security camera

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:13.480
and many devices like
switches, bridges

00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:15.400
and routers are also
called as nodes.

00:04:15.400 --> 00:04:17.440
We will be dealing
about switches,

00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:19.680
bridges and routers in
the upcoming lectures.

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:21.800
Now we are done with nodes.

00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:24.680
We will concentrate on
what are communication links.

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:28.580
A communication link can be
a wired link or a wireless link. 

00:04:29.160 --> 00:04:31.800
The important point to
note about a link is that

00:04:31.800 --> 00:04:34.580
this link only carries the information.

00:04:34.580 --> 00:04:36.920
If you don't understand
anything out of this,

00:04:36.920 --> 00:04:38.460
just wait for
this example.

00:04:38.460 --> 00:04:39.920
See this example now,

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:41.520
there are two
computers.

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:43.920
We can call these two computers as nodes.

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:46.100
Why? Because these
two computers

00:04:46.100 --> 00:04:48.260
can send data as
well as receive data.

00:04:48.260 --> 00:04:51.360
Now these nodes are going to
exchange their information,

00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:53.280
but for exchanging
the information,

00:04:53.280 --> 00:04:55.040
they are depending upon this cable.

00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:56.680
Here this cable
is the link.

00:04:56.680 --> 00:04:59.600
Obviously, a cable is
a physical medium,

00:04:59.600 --> 00:05:01.660
so it comes under
wired category.

00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:04.320
So wired link carries
the information

00:05:04.320 --> 00:05:07.400
from this computer to this
computer or vice-versa.

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:09.440
But there are scenarios where,

00:05:09.440 --> 00:05:12.180
two devices wants to
communicate with each other

00:05:12.180 --> 00:05:13.900
but not with the
help of cables.

00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:17.900
Say in this scenario, these two
smart-phones wants to exchange data.

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:20.940
Say, this phone wants to
give some data to this phone.

00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:23.520
In this case there is
no physical connectivity.

00:05:23.520 --> 00:05:26.280
Then how can that
communication be established?

00:05:26.280 --> 00:05:29.000
This is possible through
wireless technologies,

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.160
if that is the case, who is
going to carry the signals?

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:35.020
Obviously, air is going
to carry the data.

00:05:35.020 --> 00:05:37.780
So here, air is
the link that

00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:40.900
carries the data from
one place to another place.

00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:44.300
So we have two kinds
of communication links

00:05:44.300 --> 00:05:47.080
one is a wired link and
another one is a wireless link.

00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:49.220
And the link only
carries the information.

00:05:49.220 --> 00:05:50.560
We shall see some examples.

00:05:51.060 --> 00:05:53.580
Cable is a best example for wired link

00:05:53.580 --> 00:05:55.900
and air is the best example for wireless link.

