00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:16.620
Now what are all the devices
or nodes involved in the network?

00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:20.260
This printer is a node,
desktop computers are nodes,

00:06:20.260 --> 00:06:23.420
tablet is a node,
this smart-phone is a node,

00:06:23.420 --> 00:06:26.720
cellphone tower is a node,
this wireless router is a node,

00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:28.660
router, internet cloud, et cetera.

00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:32.440
See there are lots of nodes
involved in this internet cloud.

00:06:32.440 --> 00:06:36.480
In reality, internet contains lots of intermediary devices,

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:40.440
these all are intermediary devices
and these all are end devices.

00:06:40.440 --> 00:06:42.440
Why we call this as end device?

00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:45.980
Because this will be either the
starting point of the communication

00:06:45.980 --> 00:06:48.080
or the end point in
the communication.

00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:54.440
Say for example, if this computer wants
to access www.nesoacademy.org,

